Abiodun Nejo, Ado Ekiti The former Senate spokesman, Adedayo Adeyeye, has urged Nigerians – especially workers, to continue to support governments at all levels in the fight against the COVID-19 pandemic. Adeyeye stressed that compliance with the various protocols of government and the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control would prevent the spread of the disease and as well see to its end. This was contained in a statement signed by the former lawmaker’s Personal Assistant, Ayomide Arotolu, in Ado Ekiti, on Sunday. Adeyeye said, “I believe that the Almighty God will intervene in the pandemic.” He lauded health workers for their commitment in the fight against the disease. He expressed gratitude to Nigerian workers for their “patience, resilience and dogged determination in the face of dwindling world economic fortunes as a result of COVID-19 pandemic.” Copyright PUNCH.
